As Anita wrote to Dr. Math
On 08/19/2004 at 13:31:02 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>If you sell something and agree to take say 6000.00 flat and your 
>sales tax should be 7%.  What is the easiest way to figure out what 
>your sales tax would be and what your purchase price would be?
>
>[Difficulty]
>Trying to figure out if  _____ X 7% = ___________  
>Then 6000.00 - answer to get amount of sales tax and purchase price.
>
>[Thoughts]
>6000 divided by 7%.  Does not work.  

Thanks for writing to Ask Dr. Math, Anita!

6000 is 107% of the purchase price, so divide by 107% or 1.07.

Feel free to reply if I can help further with this question.


